{"lemma":"إِناث","slug":"إِناث","root":"#.ن.ث","root_slug":"_-ن-ث","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ن-ث","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1316"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A5%D9%90%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AB"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of أُنْثَى (ʔunṯā)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔi.naːθ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1316","headword_ar":"اـِنَاثٌ","root":"Anv","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Inanimate things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, T, M, K;) as trees and stones (T, K) and wood. (T.) In the passage of the Kur mentioned above,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inaAvFA","text_ar":"اـِنَاثًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to have this meaning: (T, M:) [or it there means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"females;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] Fr says that El-Lát and El-'Ozzà and the like were said by the Arabs to be feminine divinities. (T, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Small stars."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And [the dual]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^unovayaAni","text_ar":"الاُنْثَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two testicles;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxuSoyataAni","text_ar":"الخُصْيَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxuSoyaAni","text_ar":"الخُصْيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is said by some to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the scrotum;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the former is generally, though app. not always, meant by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAnvyAn","text_ar":"الانثيان"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, Mgh, Msb.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two ears:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, S, M, A, Mgh, K:) because they are of the fem. gender. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two tribes of Bejeeleh and Kudá'ah."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unovayaA Alfarasi","text_ar":"اُنْثَيَا الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The inner parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~abalataAni","text_ar":"الرَّبَلَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the thighs of the horse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^unovay","text_ar":"الاُنْثَي"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used to signify (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"engine of war called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manojaniyq","text_ar":"مَنْجَنِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":"; because the latter word is [generally] of the feminine gender. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["T","K","M","As","S","A","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}